Grammy Nominations: Jazz singer Esperanza Spalding is the surprise choice in the Breakthrough Artist category.
Act at the request of a president and possibly people will notice you.
Esperanza Spalding, the 26-year-old bassist and jazz singer personally selected by President Obama to perform at his Nobel Peace Prize ceremony in 2009, was one of the surprises of the Grammys this year with a high-level nomination in the category of Best New Artist.
