In a landmark 1966 ruling, the U.S. Supreme Court overturned the conviction of a Cleveland osteopath, Dr. Sam Sheppard, for the murder of his wife, saying in its decision, in Sheppard v. Maxwell, that there was “a carnival atmosphere in the process” due to the media.
The crime is believed to have been inspired by the television show and the film "The Fugitive".
