“This is our raw material ... we’re not going to make dirty bombs, and we’re not going to sell them to anybody.”
“We use it for research purposes, that’s all.”
However, Belarus approached the United States a few months ago, indicating interest in reaching an agreement.
Officials said the first task of removing the uranium from Belarus in October was particularly complicated, as the material had been lightly irradiated.
